olive oil
20 g butter
1 packet jasmine rice
1 bag baby broccoli
1 cucumber
¼ cup rice wine vinegar
1 packet oyster sauce
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 tsp soy sauce
1 packet pork mince
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 bag mint
2 clove garlic
1 bunch Asian Greens
1.25 cup water

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and a generous pinch of salt to the pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and all the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• While the rice is cooking, roughly chop Asian greens. Trim baby broccoli, then slice in half lengthways. Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.
• In a small bowl, combine cucumber, the rice wine vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt. Add enough water to cover the cucumber completely and stir to coat. Set aside.

• In a medium bowl, combine the oyster sauce, sweet chilli sauce, the soy sauce and a splash of water. Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and cook until softened, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl, cover to keep warm and set aside.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the veggies and oyster sauce mixture and stir to combine.

• Drain pickled cucumber.
• Divide garlic rice between bowls and top with sweet-chilli and oyster pork and veggies.
• Garnish with crushed peanuts and tear over mint. Serve with pickled cucumber. Enjoy!